  "blurb": "A four-bedroom villa set high on the Bophut hills, where bohemian styling meets Balinese architecture around an infinity pool that spills toward the horizon — with private terraces off every bedroom, open indoor-outdoor living, a private chef and daily breakfast, sleeping up to eight just above Fisherman's Village.",
  "detail": "High on the hills of Bophut, this four-bedroom villa trades on a relaxed, bohemian mood layered over Balinese architecture — polished walls, vibrant textiles and eclectic furniture set against wide island views. Four bedrooms, each with its own terrace and bathroom, sleep up to eight, and the whole house is arranged to keep the line between inside and out deliberately loose.\n\nThe centrepiece is an infinity pool that reads straight out to the horizon, framed by open-sided living and dining space and a fully equipped kitchen. Days settle into an easy rhythm here: breakfast by the water, long lunches under cover, sunsets from the pool deck.\n\nA private chef and on-site staff handle the day-to-day, with daily breakfast included and massages, babysitting, tours and vehicle rental available on request. Bophut's Fisherman's Village — its restaurants, bars and Friday walking street — sits just down the hill, with the airport and the Big Buddha only a few minutes further.",
